A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Code Section 20-8-5 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to law
2 enforcement powers of school security personnel in each public school system of the state,
3 certification, and carrying of firearms or weapons, so as to expand jurisdictional authority
4 of certain law enforcement officers to include a specified area surrounding school property;
5 to provide for a conforming change; to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws;
6 and for other purposes.
7 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
8 SECTION 1.
9 Code Section 20-8-5 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to law enforcement
10 powers of school security personnel in each public school system of the state, certification,
11 and carrying of firearms or weapons, is amended by revising subsections (a) and (c) as
12 follows:
13 "(a) In each public local school system in this state, school security personnel employed
14 by the local board of education of a county or an independent board of education of a
15 municipality for the various public schools thereof who are certified pursuant to
16 subsection (b) of this Code section and who are authorized by the such local board of
