17 education of that county or the independent board of education of that municipality shall
18 have the same law enforcement powers on school property and on public or private
19 property within five miles of school property, including the power of arrest, as law
20 enforcement officers of that respective the county or municipality in which the local school
21 system is located."
22 "(c) The provisions of this Code section shall not prohibit a local board of education of a
23 county or an independent board of education of a municipality from employing school
24 security personnel without law enforcement powers."
25 SECTION 2.
26 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
